<div class="generalitem newsitem"><strong>2013-07-26</strong> (<a href="newsitem.cgi/1374870472" title="Permanent link" rel="bookmark">#</a>) <span class="age">1 month ago</span>
<blockquote>I ordered and received an rtl-sdr stick with an HF convertor and active
antenna, planning to do some HF with it.
<p></p>
For a simple test I tried to decode APRS messages, which
<a href="http://idefix.net/~koos/newsitem.cgi/1369681707">has worked with
the Noxon dab stick and rtl_fm/multimode</a>. This new stick allows easy
connection of external antennas through an SMA connector. Besides the cable
to connect the HF convertor I also ordered an SMA - BNC cable which allowed
me to connect other antennas, such as a 2 meter antenna.
<p></p>
There were not a lot of APRS messages to test with, but eventually I found
the working settings. This stick works better with automatic gain.
<pre class="commandlog">
